messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hey, the address to my emergency, I live at 31 Grand Street, and there's a fire at somebody's house across the street.
31 Grand Avenue?
Yes, 31 Grand Avenue.
What's the address of the house on fire?
It's 28 Grand Avenue. Please, we need somebody to come over here now. The fire is out of control.
28 Grand Avenue. Is it an apartment or a house?
It's a house, the whole house is on fire!
Is anyone hurt?
There's an elderly man in the house! Hurry up!
Is everyone else out of the building?
Oh my God, I think someone's still in there!
If you're there when the fire department arrives, please let them know if anyone is still in the building, or even if you suspect somebody is in there.
Hurry, they need to get here fast!
They're on their way. Please stay calm and stay safe.
Oh my God, they're down the street. What are they doing? Get in here!
Hello? Operator? There are fire trucks down the street! The house is on fire, I don't know if everyone got out.
We're dispatching more units. Stay where you are. Do not go back inside.
911, what's your emergency?
I'm calling to report a fire at 16 Grand Avenue. The smoke is really bad.
Do you know if anyone is inside?
I'm not sure, I'm just looking from the window. I can see a lot of smoke.
Okay, we'll have the fire department out there as soon as possible.
911, what's your emergency?
There's a fire on Grant Avenue, and there are people trapped inside.
What's the address?
28 and a half Grand Avenue. There's an old couple inside.
What floor are they on?
They're on the second floor.
We have help on the way. Stay on the line with me.
911, what's your emergency?
I live near Grant Avenue, and there's a house with smoke coming from it. I don't know if it's a fire, but people are screaming.
Do you know the exact address?
It's right off Grant and Rose, before you get to Ocean.
What's the phone number you're calling from?
We'll have police and fire out there as soon as possible.
Hurry, please, there's a fire at 28 and a half Grant Avenue. The entire house is engulfed in flames. There are people inside!
Hang tight, help is on the way.
911, what's your emergency?
There's a big fire on Grant right now. An old man is in the house and he can't get out.
We have help on the way. Do you know the address?
I don't know the exact address. I just drove by and saw it.
Okay, we'll get units to the area. Thank you for calling.
